Chelsea are set to announce the signing of goalkeeper, Edouard Mendy, from Rennes next week. This was revealed by respected Italian sports journalist, Fabrizio Romano, via his Twitter account on Sunday evening. Romano tweeted, “Edouard Mendy to Chelsea is 100% done and also signed. “The announcement will be on next week.” Meanwhile, Rennes manager, Julien Stephan, on Saturday confirmed that Mendy will join Chelsea. Stephan said: “We are looking for a goalkeeper, it is no secret. “Edouard will certainly leave us to join Chelsea. “In this position, we need to get someone in very quickly. I can’t give you names as there is nothing definitive.”